    <!--/tools-->
  
    <div id="artwork-details">
    <div id="tombstone">

    <p>    Irving Penn<br />
American, 1917–2009<br />
    </p>
    <h3><em>Chimney Sweep (B), London</em>, 1950, printed 1967</h3>

    <p>
    Platinum-palladium print, edition 5/27<br />    49.3 x 37.5 cm (image); 57 x 45.5 cm (paper)<br />    Inscribed verso: “SWEEP, LONDON 1950”; inscribed verso: “P485 / .. [in a circle]”; inscribed verso: “5/27”; inscribed verso: “Platinum-palladium / Print made 1967”; signed and stamped verso: “Irving Penn / Hand-coated by the photographer [in a circle]”; stamped verso: “Deacidified to pH 8.5 9.5”; stamped and inscribed verso: “PHOTOGRAPH BY IRVING PENN / Copyright © 1951 by THE CONDE NAST PUBLICATIONS LTD / Not to be reproduced without / written permission of the / copyright owner.”; stamped and inscribed verso: “In addition to 27 prints of this / image in platinum metals, unnumbered, but signed, silver prints not exceeding a total of 4 may exist. / I.P.”<br />    Gift of Irving Penn, 1996.263</p>
        Copyright Condé Nast Publications, Inc.
        <!--<p id="dept-gallery">--><!--<br />-->
         <!--</p>-->
    </p>
    </div><!--/tombstone-->

  </div>
  <!--/artwork-details-->

    
      <div id="artwork-body">
                <div id="abbrev">
      <p><a href="http://www.artic.edu//aic/collections/exhibitions/IrvingPennArchives/artwork/more" class="more">Exhibition, Publication and Ownership Histories</a></p>
      <!--content hidden-->
    </div>
    <div id="extended">
      <p><a href="http://www.artic.edu//aic/collections/exhibitions/IrvingPennArchives/artwork/less" class="less">Exhibition, Publication and Ownership Histories</a></p>
            <h2>Exhibition History</h2>
      <p>Chicago, Art Institute of Chicago, “Irving Penn, A Career in Photography,” November 22, 1997–February 1, 1998; traveled to St. Petersburg, Russia, State Hermitage Museum, March 1–May 16, 1998; Hamburg, Germany, Deichtorhallen, June 18–September 6, 1998; Munich, Germany, Müchner Stadtmuseum, October 6, 1998–February 21, 1999; San Francisco, California, Friends of Photography/Ansel Adams Center for Photography, November 11, 1999–January 23, 2000; Museum of Fine Arts, Houston, March 25–June 4, 2000; Paris, France, Maison Européenne de la Photographie, September 13–November 5, 2000. (Colin Westerbeck)<br />
<br />
Chicago, Art Institute of Chicago, Gallery 10 Permanent Collection Rotation, May–October, 2012.</p>
                  <h2>Publication History</h2>
      <p>Sobieszek, Robert A. 1983. "Particulars: Selections from the Miller-Plummer Collection of Photography." Exh. cat. International Museum of Photography at George Eastman House. p. 23, pl. 64. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Szarkowski, John. 1984. "Irving Penn." Exh. cat. Museum of Modern Art/New York Graphic Society Books. pl. 84. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Museum Ludwig. 1984. “Sammlung Gruber: Photographie des 20. Jarhunderts.” Exh. cat. Museum Ludwig. p. 340. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Foresta, Merry A. and William F. Stapp. 1990. “Irving Penn: Master Images.” Exh. cat. National Museum of American Art and National Portrait Gallery/Smithsonian Institution Press. p. 35, cat. 22. (other print of this image)<br />
<br />
Westerbeck, Colin. 1997. “Irving Penn: A Career in Photography.” Exh. cat. Art Institute of Chicago/Bulfinch Press. p. 123, cat. 62, pl. 73.<br />
<br />
Heckert, Virginia and Anne Lacoste. 2009. “Irving Penn: Small Trades.” Exh. cat. J. Paul Getty Museum. pl. 20. (other print of this image)</p>
                  <h2>Ownership History</h2>
      <p>Given by the artist to the Art Institute, 1996.</p>
          </div>
